  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4509",
  "title": "fix(infiniteHits): compute `isLastPage` based on cached pages",
  "body": "This fixes a bug in the `infiniteHits` widget where the `isLastPage` value could conflict with the cached state.\r\n\r\n## Reproduction\r\n\r\nAssume you have an `infiniteHits` widget with a `pagination` widget (which can happen when you want better SEO).\r\n\r\n1. Click page 3\r\n2. Click page 1\r\n3. Click \"Show more results\"\r\n4. Notice you're on page 4 which doesn't exist\r\n\r\n[See reproduction →](https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-infinitehits-page-bug-pyd4v)\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\nWe now don't rely only on the helper state but also on the cached state. If the last page has been cached in the `infiniteHits` cache, we consider `isLastPage` to be `true`.",
